      "source": "evaluator",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:\n\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n}\n\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n}\n\nany idea why it's overlapping on small screens?"
    },
    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the overlapping issue is likely due to the flexbox properties not behaving as expected on mobile. You might need to adjust the flex properties and add some responsive design tweaks to ensure the product image and title don't overlap. Here's a possible solution:\n\n```css\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  .product-header {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    padding: 10px;\n  }\n\n  .product-image {\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis media query targets screens with a maximum width of 600px (typical for mobile devices) and adjusts the padding and margins accordingly. The `margin-bottom` on the `.product-image` should prevent it from overlapping the `.product-title`. Give it a try and see if it resolves the issue. If not, we might need to dig deeper into the CSS.",
